transcription.message: Hello, Thank you for calling Athena Health clinic. If this is a medical emergency please hang up now and dial nine one one. Otherwise, How can I help you today?
Hey, I would like to book an appointment for May, May 2026. Do we have any available slots for that date?
Hey there! I'd be happy to help you schedule an appointment. Just to clarify, are you a new patient with us, or have you visited our clinic before?
This is my first appointment and I did not visit the clinic yet.
Perfect! Since you're a new patient, I'll need to collect some information to get you set up in our system. Let's start with your first name  what's your first name?
Toni.
Great, thank you Toni. And what's your last name?
Vamos all.
I want to make sure I get that spelled correctly. Could you please spell your last name for me?
P as in Peter, E as in Adam, M as in Mary, A as in Adam, R as in Robert, A as in Adam. Pamela.
Got it, so that's P-E-M-A-R-A, Pemara. Is that correct?
P-E-M-A
Thank you for clarifying. So your last name is P-E-M-A, Pema. Is that right?
P as in Peter, A as in Adam, M as in Mary, A as in Adam, R as in Robert, A
Okay, so that's P-A-M-A-R-A, Pamara. Did I get that right?...
as in Adam Yes. Yes
Perfect, thank you! So your name is Toni Pamara. Now, what's your date of birth?
Just to confirm, is that April sixth, nineteen ninety?
Yes, ma'am.
Great! And last thing  would you like me to use the phone number you're calling from, or would you prefer to provide a different number?
A different number?
Sure, what phone number would you like me to use for your record?
Just give me a second. It's 224-554-9339.
Let me get you registered

Excellent! I've got you all set up in our system, Toni. Now, you mentioned you'd like to book an appointment for May twenty twenty-six. That's quite a ways out! Could you give me a specific date in May that you're looking for, or would you like me to check what's available early in the month?
Not early in the month, but do we have anything in April then?
Sure! Let me check April twenty twenty-six for you. What date in April would work best for you?
Maybe April 16th?
Let me check availability for that date.

I apologize, but our scheduling system only allows appointments to be booked up to ninety days in advance. April twenty twenty-six is beyond that window. Would you like to schedule something within the next three months instead? I can check availability for dates coming up soon.
February?
Absolutely! February works perfectly. What date in February would you prefer for your appointment?
February 30th?
I appreciate you checking, but February doesn't have a thirtieth day  it only goes up to the twenty-eighth this year. Would you like to choose another...
Okay.
Would you...
February.
What date in February would work for you? Just keep in mind February goes up to the twenty-eighth.
February 6th?
Let me check what's available.
Great news! I have availability on Friday, February sixth. I have both morning and afternoon slots available. Would you prefer a morning or afternoon appointment?
Afternoon?

I'm sorry, I don't have a three thirty slot available on that day. For the afternoon, I have two o'clock, two fifteen, two thirty, two forty-five, four o'clock, and four fifteen. Which of those times would work best for you?
Perfect! Before I confirm, may I ask the reason for your visit? This helps us better prepare for your appointment.
General checkup
Excellent. Just to confirm, you'd like to schedule an appointment on Friday, February sixth, twenty twenty-six at four fifteen PM. Is that correct?
? Yes.
Great, let me book that for you.
Perfect! I've scheduled your appointment for Friday, February sixth, twenty twenty-six at four fifteen PM. You should receive a confirmation shortly. Is there anything else I can help you with today?
That should be it thank you.
You're very welcome, Toni! We look forward to seeing you in February. Have a wonderful day!
Thank you for calling Athena Health clinic. How may I assist you today?
Hi, I need to reschedule my appointment that's coming up.
I'd be happy to help you reschedule. Can you please provide me with your name and date of birth?
Sarah Johnson, March 15th, 1985.
Thank you, Sarah. I see you have an appointment scheduled for December 3rd at 2 PM. What date would work better for you?
Can I get something next week? Maybe Thursday or Friday?
Let me check our availability. I have Thursday, December 12th at 3:30 PM or Friday, December 13th at 10:00 AM. Which would you prefer?
Thursday at 3:30 works perfectly.
Perfect! I've rescheduled your appointment to Thursday, December 12th at 3:30 PM. You'll receive a confirmation text shortly. Is there anything else I can help you with?
No, that's all. Thank you so much!
You're very welcome, Sarah! Have a great day!
Good morning! Thank you for calling Athena Health clinic. How can I help you today?
Hi, I'm calling to cancel my appointment.
I can help you with that. May I have your name and phone number, please?
Michael Brown, 555-0125.
Thank you, Michael. I see you have an appointment scheduled for November 30th at 11:00 AM. May I ask the reason for the cancellation?
I have a work conflict that came up unexpectedly. I might need to reschedule for next month.
I understand. Would you like me to help you reschedule for December, or would you prefer to call back later when you have your schedule confirmed?
I'll call back once I know my schedule. Just cancel this one for now.
No problem at all. I've cancelled your appointment for November 30th. When you're ready to reschedule, just give us a call and we'll find a time that works for you.
Great, thank you.
You're welcome, Michael. Take care and we hope to see you soon!
Hello! Thank you for calling Athena Health clinic. How can I help you?
Hi, I need to refill my prescription.
I can help you with that. May I have your name and date of birth?
Emily Davis, July 14th, 1988.
Thank you, Emily. What medication do you need refilled?
It's my blood pressure medication, Lisinopril 10mg.
I see that prescription in your file. Let me check with your pharmacy. Which pharmacy would you like us to send this to?
CVS on Main Street, please.
Perfect. I've sent the refill request to CVS on Main Street. It should be ready for pickup in about 2 hours. Is there anything else I can help you with today?
No, that's all. Thank you!
You're welcome, Emily! Have a great day!
Good morning! Athena Health clinic, how may I assist you today?
Hello, I'm wondering what your clinic hours are?
I'd be happy to help you with that. Our clinic hours are Monday through Friday from 8:00 AM to 6:00 PM. On Saturdays, we're open from 9:00 AM to 2:00 PM. We're closed on Sundays.
Great! And do you accept walk-ins or is it appointment only?
We do accept walk-ins during our regular hours, though we recommend scheduling an appointment to minimize wait times. Walk-ins are seen on a first-come, first-served basis.
Perfect. One more question - do you accept Blue Cross insurance?
Yes, we do accept Blue Cross Blue Shield. We accept most major insurance plans. If you'd like, I can verify your specific coverage when you come in for your visit.
That's great to hear. Thank you so much for the information.
You're very welcome! Is there anything else I can help you with today?
No, that's all. Have a good day!
You too! Thank you for calling Athena Health clinic!
Thank you for calling Athena Health clinic. How can I help you today?
Hi, I need to schedule a follow-up appointment with Dr. Nelson.
I'd be happy to help you schedule that follow-up. May I have your name and date of birth please?
Robert Wilson, September 30th, 1965.
Thank you, Mr. Wilson. I see you had a visit on November 15th. When would you like to schedule your follow-up?
Dr. Nelson said I should come back in two weeks. So sometime next week would be good.
Perfect. Let me check Dr. Nelson's availability for next week. I have Tuesday at 2:00 PM, Wednesday at 10:30 AM, or Thursday at 3:45 PM. Do any of those work for you?
Wednesday at 10:30 would be ideal.
Excellent! I've scheduled your follow-up appointment with Dr. Nelson for Wednesday, December 4th at 10:30 AM. You'll receive a confirmation text shortly.
Perfect. Do I need to bring anything or do any prep work?

For a follow-up, just bring your insurance card and a list of any medications you're currently taking. If Dr. Nelson requested any specific tests or preparations, that should be noted in your patient portal.
Okay, great. Thank you so much!
You're very welcome, Mr. Wilson! We look forward to seeing you on December 4th. Have a wonderful day!
